<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10326&amp;p=115722#p115722</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10326&amp;p=115722#p115722"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Conway's Life simulator for NES]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10326&amp;p=115722#p115722"><![CDATA[
<img src="http://nova.themonkeybob.net/rsc/conwayslife.png" alt="Image" /><br />Instead of trying to see how Video Life manages to be fast, I figured I would see how fast I could make a Life simulator by just using repetitive, fast code and using unofficial opcodes. It's pretty bare-bones so far and all you can do is move a cursor around to toggle cells and start/stop simulation, but I'm hoping to add onto it and have an option for a bigger grid because 32x32 isn't even big enough for the Gosper glider gun. SNES mouse support would also be cool, but I would require an emulator that both supports the mouse and doesn't choke on unofficial opcodes first.<br /><br /><a href="http://novasquirrel.com/dl/NESLife.zip" class="postlink">Download (with source)</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3838">NovaSquirrel</a> — Sat Jul 27, 2013 1:53 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
